ISLAMABAD, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan extended its deepest condolences and sympathies to the government and people of Greece over the loss of precious lives in a deadly train collision in the country, the Pakistani Foreign Ministry said on Wednesday. "We pray for the quick recovery of those injured in the incident," the ministry said in a statement. The death toll from the collision of two trains in central Greece on Tuesday night has increased to 36, while 66 injured people were still hospitalized.  â– 